Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum recorded a triple-double with 33 points, nine assists, and eight rebounds.
Derrick White scored 26 points for Boston.
Sam Hauser hit five 3-pointers and scored 15 points.
Julius Randle led Minnesota with 27 points, eight rebounds, and seven assists.
Naz Reid added 20 points off the bench.
Jaden McDaniels had 19 points and eight rebounds.
Tatum hit the second of two free throws, then drained 3-pointers on Boston's next two possessions, part of a 16-6 run to close the second quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: Anthony Edwards' 3-pointer fell short at the buzzer, missing the chance to send the game into overtime.
